'''Felipe Alves Fran<U+00E7>a da Silva''' (born May 14, 1987 in [[Suzano]], [[S<U+00E3>o Paulo (state)|S<U+00E3>o Paulo]]) is a breaststroke swimmer from [[Brazil]], who competed for his country at the [[Swimming at the 2008 Summer Olympics|2008 Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a profile on Sports Reference|work=Sports Reference|year = 2012|url = http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/fr/felipe-franca-silva-1.html|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}</ref>

He started in [[Esporte Clube Uni<U+00E3>o Suzano]], at three years old. At age 13, he was champion in Brazilian Children category II. After passing through the academy [[Gustavo Borges]] in [[Curitiba]], France moved to the capital, [[S<U+00E3>o Paulo]], and entered the [[Esporte Clube Pinheiros]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a History|work=Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a-Official Site|year = 2013|url = http://www.felipefranca.com.br/historia.html|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref>

==2008==

In 2008, he was in [[2008 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m)]], in the city of [[Manchester]] in April, where he finished 6th in the 4x100m medley <ref>{{cite web | title = Results of the 4x100m medley relay at 2008 Manchester | work = OmegaTiming | date = April 13, 2008 | url = http://www.omegatiming.com/File/Download?id=0001080E0064000000FFFFFFFFFFFF01|accessdate = April 4, 2013}}</ref> 12th in 100 meter breaststroke <ref>{{cite web | title = Results of the 100m breaststroke at 2008 Manchester | work = OmegaTiming | date = April 9, 2008 | url = http://www.omegatiming.com/File/Download?id=0001080E000D000000FFFFFFFFFFFF01|accessdate = April 4, 2013}}</ref> and 13th in 50 meters breaststroke.<ref>{{cite web | title = Results of the 50m breaststroke at 2008 Manchester | work = OmegaTiming | date = April 12, 2008 | url = http://www.omegatiming.com/File/Download?id=0001080E0051000000FFFFFFFFFFFF01 |accessdate = April 4, 2013}}</ref>

Later, in May, Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a obtained the index to [[2008 Summer Olympics]] at 100 meter breaststroke, with a time of 1m01s17, getting the second  Brazil vacancy.<ref>{{cite web|title = Rain of Olympic index,  and more than fierce fight for places in the 100m breaststroke|work=Globoesporte|date = May 10, 2008|url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/Esportes/Pequim2008/Noticias/0,,MUL465460-9823,00-CHUVA+DE+INDICES+OLIMPICOS+E+BRIGA+MAIS+QUE+ACIRRADA+PELAS+VAGAS+NOS+M+PEIT.html|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title = In thrilling finale, Henrique Barbosa and Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a are guaranteed in Beijing|work=Globoesporte|date = May 11, 2008|url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/Esportes/Pequim2008/Noticias/0,,MUL465660-9823,00-EM+FINAL+EMOCIONANTE+HENRIQUE+E+FELIPE+FRANCA+SE+GARANTEM+EM+PEQUIM.html|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref> However, he failed to pass heats.<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a stay on heats at 100m breast|work=UOL|date = July 27, 2011|url = http://esporte.uol.com.br/natacao/ultimas-noticias/2011/07/27/felipe-franca-conquista-o-ouro-nos-50-m-peito-no-mundial-de-xangai.htm|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref> He was in 22 th place in the 100 meter breaststroke, and participating in the 4x100m medley relay, got the 14th place.<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a profile on Sports Reference|work=Sports Reference|year = 2012|url = http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/fr/felipe-franca-silva-1.html|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}</ref>

==2009==

At the 2009 Brazilian Championships (Maria Lenk Trophy) he became the first swimmer to swim under 27-seconds in the long-course 50m breaststroke, winning the event with the [[World record progression 50 metres breaststroke|World Record]] of 26.89.<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a beats the 50m breaststroke world record at Maria Lenk Trophy|work=Globoesporte|date = May 8, 2009|url = http://oglobo.globo.com/esportes/felipe-franca-bate-recorde-mundial-dos-50m-peito-no-trofeu-maria-lenk-3166287|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbda.org.br/especiais/marialenk2009/materia.php?mat_id=10461|title=Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a makes history with world record|author=Eliana Alves / Souza Santos|publisher=CBDA|date=May 8, 2009|accessdate=April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref> 

On July 10, 2009, participating in the [[2009 Summer Universiade]] in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]], won the silver medal in the 50 meter breaststroke.<ref>{{cite web | title = Universiade Results | work = Swim Rankings | year = 2012 | url = http://www.swimrankings.net/index.php?page=meetDetail&meetId=532343&gender=1&styleId=12|accessdate = April 4, 2013}}</ref>

In the [[2009 World Aquatics Championships]], at [[Rome]], after a tough competition, Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a won the silver, doing 26s76 mark, Americas record. The gold went to South African [[Cameron van der Burgh]], which became the new world record holder, with 26s67.<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a gets silver on 50m breast and collapses in tears on the podium|work=Globoesporte|date = July 29, 2009|url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/Esportes/Noticias/Esportes_Aquaticos/0,,MUL1247309-16315,00-FELIPE+FRANCA+VOLTA+A+ESBARRAR+EM+VAN+DER+BURGH+MAS+LEVA+A+PRATA+NOS+M+PEIT.html|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref>

==2010==

At the [[2010 Pan Pacific Swimming Championships]] in [[Irvine, California]], Felipe won gold in the proof of 50 meters breaststroke.<ref>{{cite web | title = Felipe won the 50m breaststroke gold at the Pan-Pacific | work = Globoesporte | date = August 21, 2010 | url = http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/fr/felipe-franca-silva-1.html | accessdate = April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref>

In December, at the [[2010 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m)]] in [[Dubai]], Felipe won gold in the 50 meters breaststroke, beating the world record holder [[Cameron van der Burgh]] with a time of 25s95 (championship record), and the bronze in the 100 meter breaststroke with a time of 57s39.<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a bronze at Dubai|work=CBDA|date = December 16, 2010|url = http://www.cbda.org.br/noticias/mundial-de-dubai-bronze-para-felipe-kaio-e-recorde-de-campeonato-para-cielo|accessdate = April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref> Together with [[C<U+00E9>sar Cielo]], [[Guilherme Guido]] and [[Kaio Almeida]], hit the South American record of 4x100 meters medley with 3m23s12 time, getting the bronze medal.<ref>{{cite web|title = Brazilian Quartet is bronze|work=Globoesporte|date = December 19, 2010|url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/aquaticos/noticia/2010/12/brasil-se-despede-do-mundial-com-medalha-de-bronze-no-4x100m-medley.html|accessdate = April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref>

==2011==

In July 2011, during the [[2011 World Aquatics Championships]] in [[Shanghai]], Fran<U+00E7>a won the gold medal in the 50 meters breaststroke, again surpassing the world record holder [[Cameron van der Burgh]], with a time of 27.01 seconds.<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a is the world champion in the 50 meters breaststroke in Shanghai|work=Globoesporte|date = July 27, 2011|url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/aquaticos/noticia/2011/07/felipe-franca-bate-rival-sul-africano-e-arranca-titulo-mundial-nos-50m-peito.html|accessdate = April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref>

In [[2011 Pan American Games]], Felipe won gold in the 100 meter breaststroke<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a commands double at 100 m breast in Guadalajara|work=Globoesporte|date = October 16, 2011|url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/jogos-pan-americanos/noticia/2011/10/felipes-dominam-os-100m-peito-e-colocam-o-brasil-no-alto-do-podio.html|accessdate = April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref> and in the 4x100 meters medley<ref>{{cite web|title = Brazil team is gold in 4x100m medley in Guadalajara|work=Globoesporte|date = October 21, 2011|url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/jogos-pan-americanos/noticia/2011/10/cesar-cielo-brilha-e-brasil-fecha-natacao-com-ouro-no-4x100m-medley.html|accessdate = April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref>

==2012==

In April 2012, participating in the Maria Lenk Trophy in Rio de Janeiro, and in order to ensure the index for the Olympic Games [[London 2012]] and also to obtain an Olympic medal in the 100 meter breaststroke, Felipe obtained 59s63 in heats.<ref>{{cite web | title = Owners of the index advance to final | work = Sportv | date = April 26, 2012 | url = http://sportv.globo.com/site/eventos/trofeu-maria-lenk/noticia/2012/04/em-batalha-rumo-londres-donos-do-indice-avancam-final-dos-100m-peito.html|accessdate = April 4, 2013}} {{pt}}</ref> In 50 meters breaststroke, did the best time in the world at this year, 26s87, near his Americas record, 26s76.<ref>{{ cite web | title = Felipe won the 50m breaststroke and shows confidence in London | work = Sportv | date = April 27, 2012 | url = http://sportv.globo.com/site/eventos/trofeu-maria-lenk/noticia/2012/04/felipe-franca-vence-os-50m-peito-e-mostra-confianca-para-londres.html#esporte-natacao|accessdate = April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref>

It created an expectation that Felipe would have a chance to medal in the 100 meter breaststroke in [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in [[London]], due to this result . But in the Olympics, could not swim below the 1 minute, finishing in 12th place.<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a profile on Sports Reference|work=Sports Reference|year = 2012|url = http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/fr/felipe-franca-silva-1.html|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}</ref> The 59s63 mark would give him 5th place in the Olympic final, where the bronze was obtained with 59s49. The biggest Felipe's rival, Cameron Van der Burgh, won Olympic gold and broke world record at 100m breaststroke.<ref>{{cite web | title = South African breaks record and takes gold in the 100 m breaststroke | work = Terra | date = July 29, 2012 | url = http://esportes.terra.com.br/esportes-aquaticos/sul-africano-quebra-recorde-e-leva-ouro-nos-100-m-peito,a16a7656124ba310VgnCLD200000bbcceb0aRCRD.html|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}{{pt}}</ref> He also participated in the 4x100m medley, finishing in 15th place.<ref>{{cite web|title = Felipe Fran<U+00E7>a profile on Sports Reference|work=Sports Reference|year = 2012|url = http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/fr/felipe-franca-silva-1.html|accessdate =April 4, 2013}}</ref>

